ody theory, that\nexhibits Burnett effects. Insights from that model emphasize the role of\nnon-Gaussian statistics in the evaluation of Burnett transport coefficients,\nincluding the effects calculated by CS that stem from the nonlinear collision\noperator. Together, Parts I and II of this series provide a tutorial\nintroduction to projection-operator methods that should be broadly useful in\ntheoretical plasma physics. A Supplement (bundled at the end of Part II)\nprovides some technical details of the reduction of the general Burnett\nequations of Brey et al. (1981) to a one-component neutral fluid in order to\nsupport the result quoted by Brey (1983).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 Nov 2017 22:34:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Nov 2017 23:12:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 18 Jan 2018 19:41:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-26"}
